3. TLS Certificate in Kubernetes
Client Certificates for Clients
Server Certificates for Servers


Server Certificate: Kube-ApiServer, Kubelet, ETCD use to respond to client and it requires server certificate.
Kube-ApiServer - api-server.crt & api-server.key (it use to authenticate with the Https & ETCD, Kubelet)
ETCD - etcd-x-server.crt & etcd-x-server.key
Kubelet - kubelet.crt & kubelet.key


Client Certificate: Admin, Kube-Scheduler, Kube-Proxy, Kube-Controller-Manager use to contact the server and it requires client certificate
admin.crt & admin.key
scheduler.crt & scheduler.key
controller-manager.crt & controller-manager.key
kube-proxy.crt & kube-proxy.key
apiserver-kubelet-client.crt & apiserver-kubelet-client.key
apiserver-etcd-client.crt & apiserver-etcd-client.key
kubelet-client.crt & kubelet-client.key


Using Certitficate Authority we can verify and validate the client and server certificates.

Certificate Authority is not mandatory to be a single Certificate authroized, it can mulitple. 
Eg: API_Server-ETCD client and ETCD server certificate can be one CA 
and other client and server certificates can be other CA

Note: In some cases kubelet will act as server and client too.











